(9, 1, 'The solution is similar to level-order traversal of the tree. Here is the algorithm\r\n\r\n1. Check if root is NULL\r\n2. If not NULL\r\nswap left sub tree with right sub tree\r\nen-queue both left sub tree and right sub tree. do not enqueue if NULL\r\nnow pop from the queue and make that element the root.\r\n3. repeat from step 1\r\n\r\nHere is the pseudocode\r\n\r\nstruct node\r\n{\r\nvoid *data;\r\nstruct node *lchild,*rchild;\r\n};\r\ntypedef struct node Node;\r\n\r\nvoid swap(Node *root)\r\n{\r\nNode* temp;\r\ntemp = root->lchild;\r\nroot->lchild = root->rchild;\r\nroot->rchild = temp;\r\n}\r\n\r\nvoid\r\nMirrorImage(Node *root)\r\n{\r\nwhile(root || queueIsNotEmpty())\r\n{\r\nswap(root);\r\nif (root->lchild) {\r\nenqueue(queueName, root->lchild);\r\n}\r\nif (root->rchild) {\r\nenqueue(queueName, root->rchild);\r\n}\r\nroot = dequeue(queueName);\r\n}\r\n}', 'Ayush', 0, 0, '2014-08-28 22:01:30'),
