(6, '<pre>Which of the following term is used for a function defined inside a class?</pre>', '<pre>Member Variable</pre>', '<pre>Member function</pre>', '<pre>Class function</pre>', '<pre>Classic function</pre>', 'B'),
(7, '<pre>Which of the following concept of oops allows compiler to insert arguments in a function call if it is not specified?</pre>', '<pre>Call by value</pre>', '<pre>Call by reference</pre>', '<pre>Default arguments</pre>', '<pre>Call by pointer</pre>', 'C'),
(8, '<pre>How many instances of an abstract class can be created?</pre>', '<pre>1</pre>', '<pre>5</pre>', '<pre>13</pre>', '<pre>0</pre>', 'D'),
(9, '<pre>Which of the following cannot be friend?</pre>', '<pre>Function</pre>', '<pre>Class</pre>', '<pre>Object</pre>', '<pre>Operator function</pre>', 'C'),
(10, '<pre>Which of the following concepts of OOPS means exposing only necessary information to client?</pre>', '<pre>Encapsulation</pre>', '<pre>Abstraction</pre>', '<pre>Data hiding</pre>', '<pre>Data binding</pre>', 'C'),
(11, '<pre>Why reference is not same as a pointer?</pre>', '<pre>A reference can never be null.</pre>', '<pre>A reference once established cannot be changed.</pre>', '<pre>Reference doesn''t need an explicit dereferencing mechanism.</pre>', '<pre>All of the above.</pre>', 'D'),
(12, '<pre>cout is a/an __________ .</pre>', '<pre>operator</pre>', '<pre>function</pre>', '<pre>object</pre>', '<pre>macro</pre>', 'C'),
(13, '<pre>Which of the following concepts provides facility of using object of one class inside another class?</pre>', '<pre>Encapsulation</pre>', '<pre>Abstraction</pre>', '<pre>Composition</pre>', '<pre>Inheritance</pre>', 'C'),
(14, '<pre>How many types of polymorphisms are supported by C++?</pre>', '<pre>1</pre>', '<pre>2</pre>', '<pre>3</pre>', '<pre>4</pre>', 'B'),
(15, '<pre>Which of the following is an abstract data type?</pre>', '<pre>int</pre>', '<pre>double</pre>', '<pre>string</pre>', '<pre>Class</pre>', 'D'),
(16, '<pre>Which of the following concepts means adding new components to a program as it runs?</pre>', '<pre>Data hiding</pre>', '<pre>Dynamic typing</pre>', '<pre>Dynamic binding</pre>', '<pre>Dynamic loading</pre>', 'D'),
(17, '<pre>Which of the following statement is correct?</pre>', '<pre>A constructor is called at the time of declaration of an object.</pre>', '<pre>A constructor is called at the time of use of an object.</pre>', '<pre>A constructor is called at the time of declaration of a class.</pre>', '<pre>A constructor is called at the time of use of a class.</pre>', 'A'),
(18, '<pre>Which of the following correctly describes overloading of functions?</pre>', '<pre>Virtual polymorphism</pre>', '<pre>Transient polymorphism</pre>', '<pre>Ad-hoc polymorphism</pre>', '<pre>Pseudo polymorphism</pre>', 'C'),
(19, '<pre>Which of the following approach is adapted by C++?</pre>', '<pre>Top-down</pre>', '<pre>Bottom-up</pre>', '<pre>Right-left</pre>', '<pre>Left-right</pre>', 'B'),
(20, '<pre>Which of the following is correct about function overloading?</pre>', '<pre>The types of arguments are different.</pre>', '<pre>The order of argument is different.</pre>', '<pre>The number of argument is same.</pre>', '<pre>Both A and B.</pre>', 'D'),
(21, '<pre>Which of the following is correct about class and structure?</pre>', '<pre>class can have member functions while structure cannot.</pre>', '<pre>class data members are public by default while that of structure are private.</pre>', '<pre>Pointer to structure or classes cannot be declared.</pre>', '<pre>class data members are private by default while that of structure are public by default.</pre>', 'D'),
(22, '<pre>Which of the following concepts means wrapping up of data and functions together?</pre>', '<pre>Abstraction</pre>', '<pre>Encapsulation</pre>', '<pre>Inheritance</pre>', '<pre>Polymorphism</pre>', 'B'),
(23, '<pre>Which of the following concepts means waiting until runtime to determine which function to call?</pre>', '<pre>Data hiding</pre>', '<pre>Dynamic casting</pre>', '<pre>Dynamic binding</pre>', '<pre>Dynamic loading</pre>', 'C'),
(24, '<pre>How "Late binding" is implemented in C++?</pre>', '<pre>Using C++ tables</pre>', '<pre>Using Virtual tables</pre>', '<pre>Using Indexed virtual tables</pre>', '<pre>Using polymorphic tables</pre>', 'B'),
(25, '<pre>Which of the following operator is overloaded for object cout?</pre>', '<pre>>></pre>', '<pre><<</pre>', '<pre>+</pre>', '<pre>=</pre>', 'B'),
(26, '<pre>Which of the following is the correct class of the object cout?</pre>', '<pre>iostream</pre>', '<pre>istream</pre>', '<pre>ostream</pre>', '<pre>ifstream</pre>', 'C'),
(27, '<pre>Which of the following cannot be used with the keyword virtual?</pre>', '<pre>class</pre>', '<pre>member functions</pre>', '<pre>constructor</pre>', '<pre>destructor</pre>', 'C'),
(28, '<pre>Which of the following functions are performed by a constructor?</pre>', '<pre>Construct a new class</pre>', '<pre>Construct a new object</pre>', '<pre>Construct a new function</pre>', '<pre>Initialize objects</pre>', 'D'),
(29, '<pre>Which of the following problem causes an exception?</pre>', '<pre>Missing semicolon in statement in main().</pre>', '<pre>A problem in calling function.</pre>', '<pre>A syntax error.</pre>', '<pre>A run-time error.</pre>', 'D'),
(30, '<pre>Which one of the following options is correct about the statement given below? The compiler checks the type of reference in the object and not the type of object.</pre>', '<pre>Inheritance</pre>', '<pre>Polymorphism</pre>', '<pre>Abstraction</pre>', '<pre>Encapsulation</pre>', 'B'),
(31, '<pre>Which of the following is the correct way of declaring a function as constant?</pre>', '<pre>const int ShowData(void) { /* statements */ }</pre>', '<pre>int const ShowData(void) { /* statements */ }</pre>', '<pre>int ShowData(void) const { /* statements */ }</pre>', '<pre>Both A and B</pre>', 'C'),
(32, '<pre>Which of the following concepts is used to implement late binding?</pre>', '<pre>Virtual function</pre>', '<pre>Operator function</pre>', '<pre>Const function</pre>', '<pre>Static function</pre>', 'A'),
(33, '<pre>Which of the following statement is correct?</pre>', '<pre>C++ allows static type checking.</pre>', '<pre>C++ allows dynamic type checking.</pre>', '<pre>C++ allows static member function be of type const.</pre>', '<pre>Both A and B.</pre>', 'D'),
(34, '<pre>Which of the following factors supports the statement that reusability is a desirable feature of a language?</pre>', '<pre>It decreases the testing time.</pre>', '<pre>It lowers the maintenance cost.</pre>', '<pre>It reduces the compilation time.</pre>', '<pre>Both A and B.</pre>', 'D'),
(35, '<pre>Which of the following ways are legal to access a class data member using this pointer?</pre>', '<pre>this->x</pre>', '<pre>this.x</pre>', '<pre>*this.x</pre>', '<pre>*this-x</pre>', 'A'),
(36, '<pre>Which of the following is a mechanism of static polymorphism?</pre>', '<pre>Operator overloading</pre>', '<pre>Function overloading</pre>', '<pre>Templates</pre>', '<pre>All of the above</pre>', 'D'),
(37, '<pre>Which of the following is correct about the statements given below?\n  All operators can be overloaded in C++.\n  We can change the basic meaning of an operator in C++.\n</pre>', '<pre>Only I is true.</pre>', '<pre>Both I and II are false.</pre>', '<pre>Only II is true.</pre>', '<pre>Both I and II are true.</pre>', 'B'),
(38, '<pre>What happens if the base and derived class contains definition of a function with same prototype?</pre>', '<pre>Compiler reports an error on compilation.</pre>', '<pre>Only base class function will get called irrespective of object.</pre>', '<pre>Only derived class function will get called irrespective of object.</pre>', '<pre>Base class object will call base class function and derived class object will call derived class function.</pre>', 'D'),
