(3, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Two women were selling marbles int the market place &#8212; 1 at 3 for a paise and other at 2 for a paise. one day both of them were obliged to return home when each had 30 marbles unsold. they put together the 2 lots of marbles and handling them over to a friend asked her to sell them at 5 for 2 paise.</p>\n<p>now they were expecting to get 25 paise for the marbles as they would have got if sold separately but much to their surprise they go only 24 paise in total.</p>\n<p>where did the 1 paise go ? can anyone explain the mystery?\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Infosys Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Puzzle', 'infosys.gif'),
(4, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Alice and Liu had some berries. The total of Alice&#8217;s berries and square of number of berries with Liu is 62. The total of Liu&#8217;s berries and square of number of berries with Alice is 176. How many berries does each of them have?\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Infosys Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Puzzle', 'infosys.gif'),
(5, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>In mathematica country 1,2,3,4&#8230;.,8,9 are nine cities. Cities which form a no. that is divisible by 3 are connected by air planes. (e.g. cities 1 &amp; 2 form no. 12 which divisible by 3 then 1 is connected to city 2). Find the total no. of ways you can go to 8 if you are allowed to break the journies.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Infosys Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Aptitiude', 'infosys.gif'),
(6, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>There is a 4 inch cube painted on all sides. This is cut down into of 1 inch cubes. What is the no of cubes which have no pointed sides?\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Infosys Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Puzzle', 'infosys.gif'),
(7, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Given an integer n, give an O(log n) algorithm to determine if n is</p>\n<p>divisible by 5 without using division or mod.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Algorithms', 'amazon.jpg'),
(8, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>A box contains 90 mts each of 100 gms and 100 bolts each of 150 gms. If the entire box weighs 35.5 kg., then the weight of the empty box is :</p>\n<p>1. 10 kg</p>\n<p>2. 10.5 kg</p>\n<p>3. 11 kg</p>\n<p>4. 11.5 kg</p>\n<p>5. None of the above\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Accenture Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Aptitiude', 'accenture.png'),
(9, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Given 2n points on a circle.find the number of ways to draw n non intersecting chords.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Google interview question', 'google.jpg'),
(10, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Given an input string S write a function which returns true if it satisfies S = nT. Basically you have to find if a given string can be represented from a substring by iterating it &#8220;n&#8221; times. n &gt;= 2</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>An example would suffice &#8211;</p>\n<p>Function should return true if</p>\n<p>1) S = &#8220;abab&#8221;</p>\n<p>2) S = &#8220;abcdabcd&#8221;</p>\n<p>3) S = &#8220;abcabcabc&#8221;</p>\n<p>4) S = &#8220;zzxzzxzzx&#8221;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Function should return false if</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>1) S = &#8220;abac&#8221;</p>\n<p>2) S = &#8220;abcdabbd&#8221;</p>\n<p>3) S = &#8220;abcabcefg&#8221;</p>\n<p>4) S = &#8220;zzxzzyzzx&#8221;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>It would be easy to understand if you can give an algo instead of saying use kmp or suffix tree or&#8230;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I came up with O(n*n) solution. Wondered how to do in O(n)\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Google Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Strings', 'google.jpg'),
(11, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Given a positive integer N, arrange the integers 1 to N such the position of the average of two numbers (if present) falls outside the two numbers. For example, for a<i> and a[j], if b = (a</i><i> + a[j])/2, then if a[k] = b, k &lt; i or k &gt; j.</p>\n<p>Hint :- If the average of two numbers is not an integer then we can assume that they do not have an average.<br />\n</i></p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Google Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Algorithms', 'google.jpg'),
(12, '<pre><p>There is a clock at the bottom of the hill and a clock at the top of the hill. The clock at the bottom of the hill works fine but the clock at the top doesn''t. How will you synchronize the two clocks. Obviously, you can''t carry either of the clocks up or down the hill! And you have a horse to help you transport yourself. And, the time required for going up the hill is not equal to the time required to go down the hill.</p><p></p></pre>', 'Adobe Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Puzzle', 'adobe.jpg'),
(13, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Check Whether binary representation of number is palindrome or not  example</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>1001 =9 is palindrome</p>\n<p>1010=10 not a palindromic</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>give efficient solution..??\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Adobe Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Algorithms', 'adobe.jpg'),
(14, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>What does the following function return?</p>\n<p></p>\n<pre><br />\nint foo(int n) {<br />\nint d = n, s = n;<br />\nwhile (d) {<br />\nd = floor(d/2);<br />\ns -= d;<br />\n}<br />\nreturn s;<br />\n}<br />\n</pre>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about CPuzzles', 'amazon.jpg'),
(15, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<pre><br />\n#include&lt;stdio.h&gt;<br />\n#define MAX          10<br />\n#define MAXLEN       MAX+1<br />\n<br />\nint main()<br />\n{<br />\nprintf("%d", MAXLEN * 10);<br />\ngetchar();<br />\nreturn 0;<br />\n}<br />\n</pre>\n<p></p>\n<p>Output??</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>        a) 110</p>\n<p>b) 20</p>\n<p>c) 100</p>\n<p>d) 101\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Wipro Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about CPuzzles', 'wipro.jpg'),
(16, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>name of the part of compiler that keeps track of variable names and their attributes.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Wipro Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Terminology', 'wipro.jpg'),
(17, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Traverse a tree in preorder fashion\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Wipro Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Trees', 'wipro.jpg'),
