(58, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>You have been given pointers of 2 nodes A and B inside a Binary Search Tree. If the nodes A&#8217;s and B&#8217;s common ancestor is P,then&#8211;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>a)Write an algo to find pointer of P &#8212;if the tree node structure contains the pointer of its two children and the pointer of its parent.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>b)Write an algo to find pointer of P &#8212; if the tree node structure contains the pointer of its two childs only.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>PS: Ur algo should pass the negative test case if the A and B doesn&#8217;t come under same tree, they are on different tree.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Oracle Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Trees', 'oracle.jpg'),
(59, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>In a factory, &#8216;a&#8217; men work &#8216;b&#8217;  hours a day and produce &#8216;c&#8217; articles each day. If &#8216;d&#8217; men are released, how many hours a day will the remaining men have to work to produce &#8216;c&#8217; articles each day?</p>\n<p>1]ab/d    2]ab/b    3]a-d/b    4]ab/a-d\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Oracle Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Puzzle', 'oracle.jpg'),
