(65, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>You are given an array of positive integers. Convert it to a sorted array with minimum cost (minimum number of operations). Only valid operation are</p>\n<p>1) Decrement -&gt; cost = 1</p>\n<p>2) Delete an element completely from the array -&gt; cost = value of element</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>For example:</p>\n<p>4,3,5,6, -&gt; cost 1  //cost is 1 to make 4-&gt;3</p>\n<p>10,3,11,12 -&gt; cost 3 // cost 3 to remove 3\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Algorithms, Arrays', 'amazon.jpg'),
