(165, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Pairs of primes separated by a single number are called prime pairs. Examples are 17 and 19. Prove that the number between a prime pair is always divisible by 6.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Microsoft Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Puzzle', 'microsoft.png'),
(166, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Assume you have an array that contains a number of strings (perhaps char * a[ 100]). Each string is a word from the dictionary. Your task, described in high-level terms, is to devise a way to determine and display all of the anagrams with in the array (two words are anagrams if they contain the same characters; for example, tales and slate are anagrams\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Microsoft Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Algorithms', 'microsoft.png'),
(167, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Consider a right angled Triangle ABC, right angled at B. Length of side A (side opposite to angle A)is given. Write a function to find the lengths of side B and side C. The function should take the inputs ( Length of side A and one acute angle either B or C in radians).</p>\n<p>1. Write all test cases.</p>\n<p>2. Avoid division by zero.</p>\n<p>3. Give different ways to implement cosine and sine functions. which one is best and why.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Microsoft Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Algorithms', 'microsoft.png'),
(168, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Question 2 / 3</p>\n<p>In a special type of Binary tree 2 conditions are followed:</p>\n<p>All leaf nodes have value as the character &#8216;L&#8217; and all the non-leaf nodes have the value as character &#8216;N&#8217;.</p>\n<p>Also, each node is has either 0 or 2 children.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The tree to the left is an example tree.</p>\n<p>You are supposed to implement a function namely, constructTree. This function takes a string representing the pre-order traversal of the tree as an argument and returns the pointer to the root node of the binary tree constructed </p>\n<p></p>\n<p>PS: Do not print anything, just construct the tree and return the root node. The sample test cases below would output the pre-order of the tree returned to help you check if the tree is rightly constructed.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (0 - 2 Years)', 'amazon.jpg'),
(169, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Given a set S, find all the maximal subsets whose sum &lt;= k. For example, if S = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5} and k = 7</p>\n<p>Output is: {1, 2, 3} {1, 2, 4} {1, 5} {2, 5} {3, 4}</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Hint:</p>\n<p>- Output doesn&#8217;t contain any set which is a subset of other.</p>\n<p>- If X = {1, 2, 3} is one of the solution then all the subsets of X {1} {2} {3} {1, 2} {1, 3} {2, 3} are omitted.</p>\n<p>- Lexicographic ordering may be used to solve it\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Facebook Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Algorithms', 'facebook.jpg'),
(170, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Given two nodes of a BST and all elements in BST are distinct, write code to determine the shortest distance between the two nodes. (unit distance between two adjacent nodes). Nodes dont have parent pointer.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Trees', 'amazon.jpg'),
(171, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Find the min and max in an array. Now do it in less than 2n comparisons. (they were looking for the solution that finds both max and min in about 3/2 n comparisons).\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Facebook Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Algorithms', 'facebook.jpg'),
(172, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>You are given a list of points in the plane, write a program that outputs each point along with the three other points that are closest to it. These three points ordered by distance. The order is less then O(n^2). For example, given a set of points where each line is of the form: ID x-coordinate y-coordinate</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>1  0.0      0.0</p>\n<p>2  10.1     -10.1</p>\n<p>3  -12.2    12.2</p>\n<p>4  38.3     38.3</p>\n<p>5  79.99    179.99</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Your program should output:</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>1 2,3,4</p>\n<p>2 1,3,4</p>\n<p>3 1,2,4</p>\n<p>4 1,2,3</p>\n<p>5 4,3,1\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Facebook Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Algorithms', 'facebook.jpg'),
(173, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>How do you rotate a string of length n word by word with constant extra space in linear time (wrt n) ?\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Strings', 'amazon.jpg'),
(174, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Given 3 arrays, pick 3 nos, one from each array, say a,b,c such that |a-b|+|b-c|+|c-a| is minimum.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Algorithms, Arrays', 'amazon.jpg'),
(175, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Facebook has a feature which allows to discover the friends in common among two users. How would you implement it in a social graph?\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Algorithms', 'amazon.jpg'),
(176, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Print all the substrings of a given string. Is there any solution better than O(2^n).</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Eg: abc the possible substrings are {&#8220;a&#8221;,&#8221;b&#8221;,&#8221;c&#8221;,&#8221;ab&#8221;,&#8221;bc&#8221;,&#8221;abc}\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Strings', 'amazon.jpg'),
(177, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>A data structure is required for storing a set of integers such that each of the following operations can be done in (log n) time, where n is the number of elements in the set.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Deletion of the smallest element</p>\n<p>Insertion of an element if it is not already present in the set</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Which of the following data structures can be used for this purpose?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>A heap can be used but not a balanced binary search tree</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>A balanced binary search tree can be used but not a heap</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Both balanced binary search tree and heap can be used</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Neither balanced binary search tree nor heap can be used\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Data Structure', 'amazon.jpg'),
(178, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>There are 6 pairs of black socks and 6 pairs of white socks.What is the probability to pick a pair of black or white socks when 2 socks are selected randomly in darkness.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Aptitiude', 'amazon.jpg'),
(179, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>implement a func node *(char *word){}</p>\n<p>wich returns a link list of words dat are anagrams with the input word..if no anagrams found return NULL and add that word to the link list</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>given structure of list as</p>\n<p>struct node {</p>\n<p>struct node *next;</p>\n<p>char val[101];</p>\n<p>};\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Algorithms', 'amazon.jpg'),
(180, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Given a (Directed/Non Directed) graph and a source node and destination node . Find all the paths from a source node to the destination node. Both for directed and non-directed graph.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (0 - 2 Years) about Articles', 'amazon.jpg'),
(181, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>In how many ways 3 identical coins can be placed in 5&#215;5 grid so that no two coin come in same row and same column\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Aptitiude', 'amazon.jpg'),
(182, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Structure of a node in a binary tree is </p>\n<p></p>\n<pre><br />\ntypedef struct node* Node;<br />\nstruct node{<br />\nint data;<br />\nNode left;<br />\nNode right;<br />\nNode sibling;<br />\n}<br />\n</pre>\n<p></p>\n<p>Initially in the binary tree all the sibling pointers point to garbage values. Write a program to set these sibling pointers for each node.</p>\n<p></p>\n<pre><br />\nEg.    A<br />\n/ <br />\nB   C<br />\n/    <br />\nD   E   F<br />\nAns:<br />\nA---&gt;Null<br />\n/ <br />\nB--&gt;C--&gt;Null<br />\n/    <br />\nD--&gt;E--&gt;F--&gt;Null<br />\n</pre>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Trees', 'amazon.jpg'),
(183, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<pre>int arr[10] // in file 1</pre>\n<p></p>\n<p>Following is file 2</p>\n<p></p>\n<pre><br />\nextern int *arr<br />\nvoid foo()<br />\n{<br />\narr[0]=10;<br />\n}</pre>\n<p></p>\n<p>what kind of problem can be there?in what condition and y?\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Adobe Written test question', 'adobe.jpg'),
(184, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>The Tree Structure is</p>\n<p></p>\n<pre>                             34<br />\n/       |      <br />\n3        56      12<br />\n/                    |<br />\n89       7             22<br />\n|<br />\n78<br />\n</pre>\n<p></p>\n<p>Print elements of a n-ary tree(a tree which may have more than two elements) breadth first reverse starting with the last level</p>\n<p>nodes and up. The code need to fit the following method and interface.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>method name: void displayBFSReverse (Node head);</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Where Node implements the interface:</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>interface Node {</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>public String getNodeData ();</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>public List&lt;Node&gt; getChildren ();</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>}</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The function should return:</p>\n<p>78 22 7 89 12 56 3 34\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Google Interview Question', 'google.jpg'),
(185, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Cups are arranged in following format</p>\n<p></p>\n<pre>                              |_|<br />\n|_|    |_|<br />\n|_|   |_|   |_|<br />\n|_| |_|   |_|  |_|<br />\n|_| |_| |_|  |_|  |_|</pre>\n<p></p>\n<p>Each cup has capacity C  and once a cup gets full, it drops half extra amount to left child and half extra amount to right child</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>for Eg :   let&#8217; first cups get 2C amount of liquid then extra amount  C(2C-C) will be divided equally to left and right child cup of next level</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>i.e. C/2 to left child and C/2 to right child</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Write a function which takes input parameter as amount of liquid poured at top (L)  and height of particular cup (h) index of that cup (i) and it should return amount of liquid absorbed in that cup.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Google interview question', 'google.jpg'),
(186, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Round5 | Q2 : Suppose, Amazon have a Logging system Like This:</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>They Track all logs daily basis, stored in separate log file.Log contains a collection of tuples of Customer ID and Page ID. The length of Customer ID and Page ID is L1 and L2. Suppose We have a log of D-days , and size of each log fine can be Order of n , where n be the number of customer.</p>\n<p>In a most generalized situation, you can assume that a customer can visit the same page multiple times in a day or any number of days.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>We are interested to find out the number of Distinct customer visited at-least p distinct pages within exactly T days.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Propose a Data Structure to be use to solve this problem efficiently . Design an Algorithm to solve this problem and Find out the complexity of the algorithm.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>{Hints:- Double Hashing/ {Hashing +Tries/BST }}</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>By Sourabh (<a href="http://www.geeksforgeeks.org/archives/17629/comment-page-1#comment-7362" rel="nofollow">http://www.geeksforgeeks.org/archives/17629/comment-page-1#comment-7362</a>)\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Algorithms', 'amazon.jpg'),
(187, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Build a binary search tree using prefix traversal only.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Algorithms', 'amazon.jpg'),
(188, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Given an array of size n. It contains numbers in the range 1 to n. Each number is present at least once except for 2 numbers. Find the missing numbers.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon interview', 'amazon.jpg'),
(189, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>find maximum repeating number in a given array. optimize it for space then in time. Eg 5 is maximum repeated in array {12, 4, 5, 89, 5, 4, 12, 6, 5, 5}\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'NVIDIA Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (0 - 2 Years) about Algorithms', 'nvidia.png'),
(190, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Given  a file with billions of records data.</p>\n<p>The file is too large to in main memory,  and you need to reverse each word in that file and then save the reversed words to another file.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Facebook Interview Question', 'facebook.jpg'),
