(192, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>There is a single amoeba at time t=0.</p>\n<p>After every minute one of following can happen:</p>\n<p>1) Amoeba dies with probability 1/3</p>\n<p>2) Amoeba continues to live with probability 1/3</p>\n<p>3) Amoeba splits into two having similar behavior with probability 1/3</p>\n<p>Find out the probability that there will be no amoeba eventually.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amoeba and probabilities (Morgan Stanley Written)', 'morgan'),
