(201, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>A number is called a special number if it doesn&#8217;t contain 3 consecutive zeroes. You have to calculate the number of positive integers of exactly d digits that are special. Print your answer modulo 1000000007.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Sample Input File</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>3</p>\n<p>4</p>\n<p>3</p>\n<p>31</p>\n<p>Sample Output File</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>8991</p>\n<p>900</p>\n<p>334647494\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Directi Coding Round 1', 'directi.jpg'),
