(307, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>1st round</p>\n<p>1. Given 2 Binary Search Trees, Merge them and create a Balanced Binary Search Tree</p>\n<p>My solution was</p>\n<p>convert each tree into DLL O(nlogn)</p>\n<p>Merge both trees into single DLL O(n)</p>\n<p>Create BST from LL O(n)</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>2. From a running stream of numbers, find the medium at any point of time.</p>\n<p>Solved with bad complexity</p>\n<p>Dont know the answer , But the interviewer gave me some hints related to heaps</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>2nd round</p>\n<p>1. Given a array of numbers , find the contiguous sub array whose sum is k</p>\n<p>Although i saw the solution here, I couldnt recollect it, I gave another solution..</p>\n<p>1.Create a parallel array , which is sum array, s<i> = sum(arr[1..i])</p>\n<p>2.find a number s</i><i>+k in the sum array, which is sorted, so binary search</p>\n<p>Overall the complexity is nlogn,</i></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>2. given a array, find all pairs of numbres whose sum is k\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Telephonic Interview Questions', 'amazon.jpg'),
