(333, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Given an array having placement of integers or characters in the given formâ€¦.</p>\n<p>a1 a2 a3 a4 a5 a6 b1 b2 b3 b4 b5 b6</p>\n<p>Write an inplace algorithm to rearrange the elements in the array likeâ€¦â€¦â€¦â€¦.</p>\n<p>a1 b1 a2 b2 a3 b3 a4 b4 a5 b5 a6 b6.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>My approach is:</p>\n<pre><code>void inplace(int a[], int n)<br />\n{<br />\nint low,high,mid,i,j,temp;<br />\nlow=1;high=n-2;<br />\nmid=(low+high)/2;<br />\nwhile(low&lt;=high)<br />\n{<br />\ni=low;j=mid+1;<br />\nwhile(i&lt;=mid)<br />\n{<br />\ntemp=a<i>;<br />\na</i><i>=a[j];<br />\na[j]=temp;<br />\ni++;j++;<br />\n}<br />\nlow++;<br />\nhigh--;<br />\n}<br />\n}</i></code></pre>\n<p>\n</p>\n<p>Is there any better approach to do it in one scan?\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Arrange in alternate', ''),
(334, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Segregate positive and negative nos in array without changing order</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>*No extra space (can use one extra space)-O(1) max</p>\n<p>*No order change allowed</p>\n<p>example:</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>input : 1,-5,2,10,-100,-2</p>\n<p>output: -5,-10,-100,1,2</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>input : -1,-5,10,11,15,-500,200,-10</p>\n<p>output : -1,-5,-10,-500,-10,10,11,15\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Microsoft Interview Question', 'microsoft.png'),
