(338, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Which one of the following is NOT a referential integrity issue in a relational database where the DEPT column of the EMPLOYEE table is designated as a foreign key into the DEPARTMENT table?</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Inserting a new row into DEPARTMENT with a primary key that is not the value of the DEPT column of any row in EMPLOYEE</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Deleting a row of DEPARTMENT</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Updating the value of DEPT in a row of EMPLOYEE with a value that is not the primary key of any of the rows in DEPARTMENT</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Inserting a new row into EMPLOYEE with a DEPT whose value is not the primary key of any of the rows in DEPARTMENT\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Oracle Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Terminology', 'oracle.jpg'),
(339, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Merge 2 sorted arrays in constant space and minimum time complexity.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Adobe Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (0 â€“ 2 Years) about Algorithms', 'adobe.jpg'),
(340, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>An array is given eg. b4a0c</p>\n<p>This represents a linked list with head a .</p>\n<p>next node is in the index 0 (bcoz 0 is next a in the array)</p>\n<p>so second node is b.</p>\n<p>b&#8217;s next node is in index 4 (bcoz 4 is next to b in the array)</p>\n<p>so third node is c. this is the last node bcoz its next index in array contains NULL</p>\n<p>therefore the linked list is a-&gt;b-&gt;c</p>\n<p>Note: a is the head bcoz its index(2) is not present in the array</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Give an <b>efficient</b> algorithm to convert the array to linked list\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'array to linked list â€“ tricky', ''),
(341, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>#define MACRO(num, str) {</p>\n<p>Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â printf(&#8220;%d&#8221;, num);</p>\n<p>Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â printf(&#8221; is&#8221;);</p>\n<p>Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â printf(&#8221; %s number&#8221;, str);</p>\n<p>Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â printf(&#8220;n&#8221;);</p>\n<p>Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â }</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>what is the use of  &#8221; &#8221; at the end of every line??\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Macro question', ''),
(342, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Find the first repeating element in an array of size n in O(n).</p>\n<p>Elements are in range.</p>\n<p>e.g 3,2,1,2,2,3</p>\n<p>The first repeating element is 3.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'First repeating element in array', ''),
(343, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>mplement a circular buffer of size N. Allow the caller to append, remove and list the contents of the buffer. Implement the buffer to achieve maximum performance for each of the operations.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The new items are appended to the end and the order is retained i.e elements are placed in increasing order of their insertion time. When the number of elements in the list elements exceeds the defined size, the older elements are overwritten.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>There are four types of commands.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>&#8220;A&#8221;  n &#8211;  Append the following n lines to the buffer. If the buffer is full they replace the older entries.</p>\n<p>&#8220;R&#8221;  n &#8211;  Remove first n elements of the buffer. These n elements are the ones that were added earliest among the current elements.</p>\n<p>&#8220;L&#8221;   &#8211; List the elements of buffer in order of their inserting time.</p>\n<p>&#8220;Q&#8221;  &#8211; Quit.  </p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Your task is to execute commands on circular buffer.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Input format :</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>First line of input contains N ,  the size of the buffer.</p>\n<p>A n  &#8211; append the following n lines to the buffer.</p>\n<p>R n &#8211; remove first n elements of the buffer.</p>\n<p>L &#8211; list the buffer.</p>\n<p>Q &#8211; Quit.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Output format :</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Whenever  L command appears in the input, print the elements of buffer in order of their inserting time. Element that was added first should appear first. </p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Sample Input :</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>10</p>\n<p>A 3</p>\n<p>Fee</p>\n<p>Fi</p>\n<p>Fo</p>\n<p>A 1</p>\n<p>Fum</p>\n<p>R 2</p>\n<p>L</p>\n<p>Q</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Sample Output :</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Fo</p>\n<p>Fum</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Constraint :</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>0 &lt;= N &lt;= 10000</p>\n<p>Number of removing elements will &lt;= number of elements presents in circular buffer.</p>\n<p>total number of commands &lt;= 50000.</p>\n<p>total number of characters in input &lt;= 20000000.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>FOR THIS QUESTION I MADE THIS CODE BUT IT IS NOT WORKING IF ANYBODY CAN', 'GET ME ERROR', ''),
(344, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Given a number N, find the next smallest number(ie larger than N) with the same digits as of N\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Directi Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Algorithms', 'directi.jpg'),
(345, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>A stack with n elements and an empty stack is provided.</p>\n<p>Return a stack with sorted values in minimum time complexity\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Sort a stack', ''),
(346, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>A sorted array is rotated any number of times now write a code to search a number in this array (without disrupting the original elements in the array)\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Microsoft Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (0 â€“ 2 Years) about Arrays', 'microsoft.png'),
(347, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>The string â€œpaypal is the faster, safer way to send moneyâ€ is written in a</p>\n<p>clockwise spiral pattern inside a square starting from the upper left</p>\n<p>corner:</p>\n<p>(you may want to display this pattern in a fixed font for better legibility).</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>P A Y P A L</p>\n<p>F E R W A I</p>\n<p>A M O N Y S</p>\n<p>S D Y E T T</p>\n<p>R N E S O H</p>\n<p>E T S A F E</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Then read line after line:</p>\n<p>PAYPALFERWAIAMONYSSDYETTRNESOHETSAFE</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Write the code that will take a string, calculate the minimum square that</p>\n<p>will contain it and return the converted string:</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>String convert(String text);</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>convert(â€œpaypalisthefastersaferwaytosendmoneyâ€) should return</p>\n<p>â€œpaypalferwaiamonyssdyettrnesohetsafeâ€\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'PayPal Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Algorithms', ''),
(348, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Given a1 a2 a3 a4&#8230;an b1 b2 b3 b4..bn c1 c2 c3..cn.</p>\n<p>Convert this array to a1b1c1a2b2c2&#8230;anbncn using O(1) space.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'convert array to given order in-order', ''),
(349, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Find the â€˜nâ€™th node as it appears in the inorder traversal of the given tree if each node</p>\n<p>contains the number of nodes in its subtree as value of node.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Tree â€“ nth node', ''),
(350, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>glitch is a walking robort moves in a peculiar problem: it takes x steps forward , then x+1 steps backward, then 2x steps forward, x+2 steps backward,3x steps forward x+3 steps backward , and so on&#8230; until it has taken y steps,glitch turns 180 degrees before continuing with its pattern . write a program that prompts x and y and total number of steps taken and outputs how many steps away from its starting point\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'FlipKart Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about C++, Data Structure', 'flipkart.jpg'),
(351, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Write the program to implement</p>\n<p>*****</p>\n<p>***</p>\n<p>*</p>\n<p>***</p>\n<p>*****\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'C PROGRAMMING', ''),
(352, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>how to delete last node of a linked list by knowing only first node in O(1) time complexity?</p>\n<p>if delete last then can we delete last second also?\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Linked List', ''),
(353, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Q1) Given that there are n players and each one of them has played exactly one game with every other player. Also given is an API that tells whether player â€˜aâ€™ won or lost to player â€˜bâ€™, where â€˜aâ€™ and â€˜bâ€™ could be any of the players. Arrange the n players in a length n array such that player at position â€˜iâ€™ has won from player at â€˜i+1â€™ and lost to player at â€˜i-1â€™.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Please help!', ''),
(354, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>How do you determine if every digit in the binary representation of a number is a one?\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Bit Magic', 'amazon.jpg'),
(355, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>given a char array, remove every third element from the array, meanwhile if there appears &#8220;a&#8221;, &#8220;b&#8221;, &#8220;d&#8221;, &#8220;e&#8221;, &#8220;g&#8221; in sequeces, remove the charactor between them. for example:  if the array is &#8220;aerbfydtyeg&#8221;, the removed array is &#8220;aebdeg&#8221;, any one have any idea?\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Qualcomm question', ''),
(356, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Write a program to remove fragment that occur in all strings,where a fragment</p>\n<p>is 3 or more consecutive word.</p>\n<p>example :</p>\n<p>input::</p>\n<p>s1 = &#8220;It is raining and I want to drive home.&#8221;;</p>\n<p>s2 = &#8220;It is raining and I want to go skiing.&#8221;;</p>\n<p>s3 = &#8220;It is hot and I want to go swimming.&#8221;;</p>\n<p>output::</p>\n<p>s1 = &#8220;It is raining drive home.&#8221;;</p>\n<p>s2 = &#8220;It is raining go skiing.&#8221;;</p>\n<p>s3 = &#8220;It is hot go swimming.&#8221;;</p>\n<p>removed fragment = &#8220;and i want to&#8221;</p>\n<p>i was told that this program will be tested again large files( in example above string are given as a sample)</p>\n<p>and then we have to remove fragment from files.so efficiency will be taken into consideration.</p>\n<p>Assumptions:Ignore capitalization ,punctuation. but preserve in output.</p>\n<p>I told him that i will map the fragment from first string and then search the others, and we actually need to consider 3 length ones only as a 4 length one will implicitly contain two 3 word phrases and the phrases can overlap.</p>\n<p>i was stuck when he gave me this kind of example</p>\n<p>a a a a a b c b c b c b c</p>\n<p>if we are removing fragment &#8220;a b c&#8221; ,then after removing middle one we got another &#8220;a b c&#8221; fragment and so on&#8230;\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'fragment removal in all files', ''),
(357, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Given a list of numbers from 1 to N(sorted). either we add or subtract X from a given range say A to B (1&lt;=A&lt;B&lt;=N) Y times. The question is find the difference b/w maximum and minimum in that list of number.</p>\n<p>Number X and the range A to B could be changed for every Y operations.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Max and MIN', ''),
(358, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>You are given a String number containing the digits of a phone number</p>\n<p>(the number of digits, n, can be any positive integer) . To help you memorize the number, you want to divide it into groups of contiguous digits. Each group must contain exactly 2 or 3 digits. There are three kinds of groups:</p>\n<p>â€¢ Excellent: A group that contains only the same digits. For example, 000 or 77.</p>\n<p>â€¢ Good: A group of 3 digits, 2 of which are the same. For example, 030, 229 or 166.</p>\n<p>â€¢ Usual: A group in which all the digits are distinct. For example, 123 or 90.</p>\n<p>The quality of a group assignment is defined as 2 Ã— (number of excellent groups) + (number of good groups)</p>\n<p>Divide the number into groups such that the quality is maximized.</p>\n<p>Design an efficient algorithm to return the solution that maximizes the quality.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Google Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Algorithms', 'google.jpg'),
(359, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>1. You have a lot of objects that it can&#8217;t be stored in memory. The objects can be indexed by a long key. You are required to implement a cache such that it&#8217;s sorted by the most recently used object.</p>\n<p>Mention what data structures do you want to use to implement this cache and please write the pseudocode for both functions:</p>\n<p>Object get(long id);</p>\n<p>void put(long id, Object obi);\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon online test for SDE', 'amazon.jpg'),
(360, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Do you know Tug of war???</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Tug of war, also known as tug o&#8217; war, is a sport that directly pits two teams against each other in a test of strength.</p>\n<p>During school days, both Chef Shifu and Chef Po are champions of tug of war. On behalf of Restaurant&#8217;s Anniversary, Chef Shifu and Chef Po decided to conduct a tug of war game with their customers.</p>\n<p>Of course Master Chef Oogway has formed the rules for the game. Let N be the number of players participating in the game, and players stand in a circle.</p>\n<p>Now the official rules formed by Master Chef Oogway are given as follows:</p>\n<p>i. There are the infinite number of long horizontal ropes. When a rope is holded by exactly two players, it is termed as Bonding.</p>\n<p>ii. At least one bonding is necessary to conduct a game.</p>\n<p>To make the game more pretty interesting, Master Chef Oogway had added some other rules as follows:</p>\n<p>iii. A player can have of more than one bonding if and only if every players who share a bonding have the same number of bondings as the player. That is, if the player A have more than one bonding, and the player A makes bonding with the player B, then the number of bondings of the player A must be the same as the number of the player B&#8217;s.</p>\n<p>iv. A player is not allowed to disturb the other&#8217;s bondings. That is, any two ropes must not be crossed.</p>\n<p>v. The number of bondings of each player must be at most K.</p>\n<p>Now Master Chef Oogway asked Chef Shifu and Chef Po, to find out the number of possible games.</p>\n<p>Input</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>First line contains T, the number of test cases. Each of T line contains 2 positive integers N and K separated by a space.</p>\n<p>Constraints:</p>\n<p>1 ? T ? 10000(104)</p>\n<p>0 ? N ? 10000 (104)</p>\n<p>0 ? K ? N</p>\n<p>Output</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>For each test case, output the number of ways to conduct the game modulo 100000000000007 (1014+7) in one line.</p>\n<p>Example</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Input:</p>\n<p>3</p>\n<p>3 2</p>\n<p>4 0</p>\n<p>2 1</p>\n', 'algorithms', ''),
(361, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>There is a straight roads with &#8216;n&#8217; number of milestones. You are given an array with the distance between all the pairs of milestones in some random Order. Find the position of milestones.</p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<p>Consider a road with 4 milestones(a,b,c,d) :</p>\n<p>a &lt;&#8212; 3Km &#8212;&gt;b&lt;&#8212; 5Km &#8212;&gt;c&lt;&#8212; 2Km &#8212;&gt;d</p>\n<p>Distance between a and b = 3</p>\n<p>Distance between a and c = 8</p>\n<p>Distance between a and d = 10</p>\n<p>Distance between b and c = 5</p>\n<p>Distance between b and d = 7</p>\n<p>Distance between c and d = 2</p>\n<p>All the above values are given in a random order say 7, 10, 5, 2, 8, 3.</p>\n<p>The output must be 3,5,2 or 2,5,3\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Algorithms', 'amazon.jpg'),
