(373, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>given width &amp; height , find the total no. of rectangles possible.  if width=3, height=3.</p>\n<p>__ __ __</p>\n<p>|__|__|__|</p>\n<p>|__|__|__|</p>\n<p>|__|__|__|</p>\n<p>In this grid, there are 4 2&#215;3 rectangles, 6 1&#215;3 rectangles and 12 1&#215;2 rectangles. Thus there is a total of 4 + 6 + 12 = 22 rectangles. Note we don&#8217;t count 1&#215;1, 2&#215;2 and 3&#215;3 rectangles because they are squares.</p>\n<p>width &amp; height will be less than 1000.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Count Rectangles of given width and height', ''),
