(442, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>There is 8 digit phone no. in which 1st digit indicate total no. of 0&#8242;s in the no.,2nd digit indicate total no. of 1&#8242;s in the no â€¦.. so on find the no which satisfy this property?&#8230;&#8230;.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'puzzle', ''),
(443, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>you are given a linked list write a program that reverse every elemet in the linked list</p>\n<p>if  N=2, &#8220;,a-b-c-d-e-f-g&#8221; convert to b-a-d-c-f&#8211;e-a</p>\n<p>if N=3, &#8220;a-b-c&#8211;d-e-f-g&#8221; convert to &#8220;c-b-a-f-e-d-g&#8221;\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'micrsoft', ''),
(444, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>With out using any sorting method sort the given array and you are also not allowed to take any auxilary array.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Interview question', ''),
(445, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>An efficient way to convert Binary tree to BST?\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Binary Tree to BST conversion', ''),
(446, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>1). Given an array and an integer X. Find all pairs (a,b) such that a+b=X.</p>\n<p>Only positive numbers considered.</p>\n<p>Expected Comp. : O(n)\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview 1st Round', 'amazon.jpg'),
(447, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>two 32bit integers m,n are given.replace all the bits in m from i to j locations with all the bits in n from k to l locations&#8230;.</p>\n<p>eg. m = 110000000000 n = 10101010 i=3 j=5 k=5 l=7</p>\n<p>o/p:110000101000\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Microsoft Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Bit Magic', 'microsoft.png'),
(448, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Find the &#8220;fixed point&#8221; of an array</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Input: an array A of *distinct* integers in ascending order. (Remember that integers can be negative!) The number of integers in A is n.</p>\n<p>Output: one position k in the list, such that A[k]=k, if any exists. Otherwise: &#8220;No&#8221;.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Algorithms', ''),
(449, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>In the given array all the elements occur single time except  one element which occurs  2 times find it in O(n) time and O(1) space.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>e.g.  2 3 4 9 3 7</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>output <img src="smileys/smile3.gif" width="" height="" alt=":3" title=":3" class="bbcode_smiley" /></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>If such a solution exist can we extend the logic to find &#8220;All the repeated elements in an array in O(n) time and O(1) space&#8221;\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Algorithms, Arrays', ''),
(450, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Copy the contents of one array A to another Array B without using loops and any other standard string copy functions\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Copy the contents of one array', ''),
(451, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>There is a stream of characters.  At any point, you can be asked to find out if the string received so far is palindrome or not.   Do it in better than O(n) and No extra space.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon interview question about strings', 'amazon.jpg'),
(452, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Seat Reservation prog for the theatre. Write a function for seat allocation for the movie tickets. Total no of seats available are 200. 20 in each row. Each row is referred by the Character, &#8220;A&#8221; for the first row and &#8216;J&#8217; for the last. And each seat in a row is represented by the no. 1-20. So seat in diffrent rows would be represented as A1,A2&#8230;.;B1,B2&#8230;..;&#8230;&#8230;..J1,J2&#8230; Each cell in the table represent either 0 or 1. 0 rep would seat is available , 1 would represent seat is reserved.</p>\n<p>Booking should start from the last row (J) to the first row(A). At the max 20 seats can be booked at a time. if seats are available, then print all the seat nos like &#8220;B2&#8243; i.e (2 row, 3 col) otherwise Print &#8220;Seats are not available.&#8221; and we must book consecutive seats only.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Seat allocation program', ''),
(453, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Assume that there are n numbers (some possibly negative) on a circle, and</p>\n<p>we wish to find the maximum contiguous sum along an arc of the circle. Give an</p>\n<p>efficient algorithm for solving this  problem.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer about Algorithms', ''),
(454, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>You have given some plates. Width of each plate is different. Plate is arrange like stack. The only operation you can do is Flip. from upward you can go on any plate and flip that. You have to arrange the Plates in sorted order.Do it in Minimum time complexity.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Microsoft MBD interview question', 'microsoft.png'),
(455, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>unsigned int a, b, c;</p>\n<p>/* a and b are assume to have some values */</p>\n<p>c = (a + b) / 2; // &lt;- There is a bug in this st</p>\n<p>What is the bug? and how you debug it?\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'how to debug  the c codeâ€¦â€¦â€¦â€¦?', ''),
(456, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Write a c program to print the permutations of the string?\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'most prevently asked interview questionâ€¦â€¦â€¦â€¦â€¦â€¦', ''),
(457, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Given an integer n, compute 2 integers x, y satisfying: n&lt;=x*y&lt;=n+2; |x-y| is minimal.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Algorithms', 'amazon.jpg'),
(458, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>The next highest number in the given sequence</p>\n<p>ex: input:213476&#8211;&gt;213467</p>\n<p>54321&#8211;&gt; -1\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (0 â€“ 2 Years)', 'amazon.jpg'),
(459, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Find the second largest element in an array with minimum no of comparisons and give the minimum no of comparisons needed on an array of size N to do the same\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (0 â€“ 2 Years) about Arrays', 'amazon.jpg'),
(460, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Input: an array A of *distinct* integers in ascending order. (Remember that integers can be negative!) The number of integers in A is n.</p>\n<p>Output: one position k in the list, such that A[k]=k, if any exists. Otherwise: &#8220;No&#8221;.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon interview question', 'amazon.jpg'),
(461, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Given an un-sorted array. Find two indices i &amp; j such that, arr<i>=arr[j] &amp; j-i is maximum.</p>\n<p>Can it be done in O(N)?<br />\n</i></p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Find two indices i & j such that, arr[i]=arr[j] & j-i is maximum.', ''),
(462, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Generate a sequence from the results of a tournament</p>\n<p>In the tournament every player will play with every other player. And the results of these matches are given to u.</p>\n<p>U need to generate a sequence such that each player will have the player to whom he has won on his left and the player to whom he has lost to his right</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>eg. consider p1,p2,p3,p4,p5</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>if p1 has won against p2 and lost with p5</p>\n<p>then p2,p1,p5 is a valid sequence </p>\n<p></p>\n<p>like wise this rule must be applicable for all the players throughout the sequence !!\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon interview question', 'amazon.jpg');
