(463, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Reverse a Linked List in size of 2</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Say LL is </p>\n<p></p>\n<p>1-&gt;2-&gt;3-&gt;4-&gt;5-&gt;6-&gt;7-&gt;8</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Then u need to return </p>\n<p></p>\n<p>7-&gt;8-&gt;5-&gt;6-&gt;3-&gt;4-&gt;1-&gt;2\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Microsoft Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Linked Lists', 'microsoft.png'),
(464, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>You have a array of int. Elements of the array are in sequential order. For example, {0,1,2,3}, {0,1,2,3,4,5}. Now, you have given an array and only one sequence is missing. How will you determine which sequence number is missing. {0,1,2,4,5,6}, Here 3 is missing. An time efficient algorithm is required.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Microsoft Interview Question for Software Engineer/Developer (Fresher) about Algorithms, Arrays', 'microsoft.png'),
(465, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Reverse stack using push, pop without any auxiliary data structure\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Mircosoft Interview Question', ''),
(466, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Given a binary tree, write a program to find the cousin nodes of the given node.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon interview question about trees', 'amazon.jpg'),
(467, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>In a matrix of characters, find an string. String can be in any way (all 8 neighbors to be considered), like find Microsoft in below matrix.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>A-C-P-<u>R</u>-C</p>\n<p>X-<u>S</u>-<u>O</u>-P-<u>C</u></p>\n<p>V-<u>O</u>-V-N-<u>I</u></p>\n<p>W-G-<u>F</u>-<u>M</u>-N</p>\n<p>Q-A-<u>T</u>-I-T</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>String <b>Microsoft</b> is present in the matrix above ?</p>\n<p>There also a slight variation where a diagonal neighbor is not considered.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Find a string inside a 2-dimensional array', ''),
(468, '<pre>\n\n		\n		<p>Given an integer expression in a prefix format (i.e. the operator precedes the number it is operating on) ,  print the expression in the post fix format .</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Example: If the integer expression is in the prefix format is *+56-78,  the postfix format expression is 56+78-*. Both of these correspond to the expression (5+6)*(7-<img src="smileys/bigeyes.gif" width="" height="" alt="8)" title="8)" class="bbcode_smiley" />\n</p>\n<p></p>\n\n		\n	</pre>', 'Amazon interview question', 'amazon.jpg');
